{"id":"220435984_The_uncertainty_relation_for_joint_measurement_of_postion_and_momentum","abstract":"We prove an uncertainty relation, which imposes a bound on any joint measurement of position and momentum. It is of the form (ΔP)(ΔQ) ≥ Ch, where the 'uncertainties' quantify the difference between the marginals of the joint measurement and the corresponding ideal observable. Applied to an approximate position measurement followed by a momentum measurement, the uncertainties become the precision ΔQ of the position measurement, and the perturbation ΔP of the conjugate variable introduced by such a measurement. We also determine the best constant C, which is attained for a unique phase space covariant measurement.","authors":["Reinhard F. Werner"],"meta":["December 2004Quantum Information & Computation 4(6):546-562","DOI:10.26421/QIC4.6-7-13","SourceDBLP"],"references":["228558292_Constructing_optimal_maps_for_Monge's_transport_problem_as_a_limit_of_strictly_convex_costs","222403668_Physical_content_of_Heisenberg's_uncertainty_relation_Limitation_and_reformulation","2188485_Universally_Valid_Reformulation_of_the_Heisenberg_Uncertainty_Principle_on_Noise_and_Disturbance_in_Measurements","312913129_On_the_translocation_of_masses","275982075_Foundations_of_Modern_Analysis","268930528_Some_Formal_Properties_of_the_Density_Matrix","266520930_Quantum_Theory_of_Open_System","266195338_The_Monge_distance_between_quantum_states","234947894_Quantum_harmonic_analysis_on_phase_space","232243107_Abstract_Harmonic_Analysis_II","226855903_Uber_den_anschaulichen_Inhalt_der_quantentheoretischen_Kinematik_und_Mechanik","226477402_Zur_Quantenmechanik_einfacher_Bewegungstypen","226127046_Die_Eindeutigkeit_der_Schrodingerschen_Operatoren","226008060_Physical_uniformities_on_the_state_space_of_nonrelativisitic_quantum_mechanics","222561136_Uncertainty_Relations_for_Joint_Measurements_of_Noncommuting_Observables","222286131_Covariant_measurements_and_uncertainty_relations","200524292_Probabi